---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Are You OK? — Kappa Alpha Psi® Fraternity, Inc.">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Are You OK?</h1>
      <p>Your health matters. Your life matters. Check in with yourself and your brothers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Crisis Line Banner -->
  <div style="background:var(--crimson); color:#FFF8E1; padding:1rem; text-align:center; font-size:0.95rem;">
    <strong>Mental Health Crisis Line:</strong> NAMI &mdash; <a href="tel:+18009506264" style="color:var(--gold); font-weight:700;">800-950-6264</a> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Text <strong>"HelpLine"</strong> to <strong>62640</strong>
  </div>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="section section--cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto; text-align:center;">
        <h2 class="section-title">About Are You OK?</h2>
        <p style="font-size:1.1rem; line-height:1.8; color:var(--text-light); margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <strong>Are You OK?</strong> is Kappa Alpha Psi's comprehensive health and wellness initiative, developed in partnership with <strong>Johnson &amp; Johnson</strong>. The program addresses the full spectrum of health — mental, physical, nutritional, and preventive — with a particular focus on the health disparities that disproportionately affect Black men and communities of color.
        </p>
        <p style="line-height:1.8; color:var(--text-light);">
          Too often, Black men are taught that seeking help is a sign of weakness. Are You OK? directly challenges that narrative — promoting a culture within Kappa Alpha Psi® and beyond where brothers check in with each other, prioritize their health, and seek help without shame.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Stats -->
  <section class="section section--crimson">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title" style="color:#FFF8E1;">Health Disparities We're Addressing</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--2" style="gap:2rem;">
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius:10px; padding:2rem; border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.3);">
          <h3 style="color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:1rem;">Mental Health</h3>
          <ul style="color:rgba(255,248,225,0.85); line-height:2.2; list-style:none; padding:0;">
            <li>🔴 <strong style="color:#fff;">21%</strong> of Black Americans experience mental illness</li>
            <li>🔴 Only <strong style="color:#fff;">39%</strong> of those affected receive care</li>
            <li>🔴 <strong style="color:#fff;">56–74%</strong> of those exposed to trauma require mental health services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius:10px; padding:2rem; border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.3);">
          <h3 style="color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:1rem;">Prostate Cancer</h3>
          <ul style="color:rgba(255,248,225,0.85); line-height:2.2; list-style:none; padding:0;">
            <li>🔴 Approximately <strong style="color:#fff;">1 in 5</strong> Black men will be diagnosed with prostate cancer</li>
            <li>🔴 Black men are <strong style="color:#fff;">2&times;</strong> more likely to die from prostate cancer</li>
            <li>🔴 Black men have a <strong style="color:#fff;">1.7&times;</strong> higher diagnosis rate than white men</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Six Resource Sections -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Six Areas of Support</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Are You OK? provides resources across six critical health domains</p>
      <div class="grid grid--3">

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="program-card-header">
            <div class="program-card-icon">🧠</div>
            <h3>Mental Health Evaluation</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="program-card-body">
            <p>Access to evidence-based mental health screening tools and assessments to help members understand their mental health status and identify when professional support may be needed. Self-assessment resources are available confidentially online.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="program-card-header">
            <div class="program-card-icon">🏥</div>
            <h3>Medical &amp; Physical Health</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="program-card-body">
            <p>Information and resources on preventive screenings, prostate health, cardiovascular disease, diabetes management, and other conditions that disproportionately affect Black men. Early detection saves lives.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="program-card-header">
            <div class="program-card-icon">🥗</div>
            <h3>Nutrition</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="program-card-body">
            <p>Practical nutritional guidance tailored to Black men's health needs — addressing the specific dietary factors that contribute to health disparities in the community while being culturally informed and realistic.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="program-card-header">
            <div class="program-card-icon">📚</div>
            <h3>Educational Resources</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="program-card-body">
            <p>A curated library of health education materials, research, and tools covering mental health, physical wellness, and preventive care — all vetted for accuracy and designed for accessibility.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="program-card-header">
            <div class="program-card-icon">🎥</div>
            <h3>Video Support</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="program-card-body">
            <p>A growing library of video content including personal testimonials from brothers who have navigated mental health challenges, expert interviews, and educational presentations on key health topics.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="program-card">
          <div class="program-card-header">
            <div class="program-card-icon">🤝</div>
            <h3>Get Involved</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="program-card-body">
            <p>Opportunities for chapters and individual brothers to host Are You OK? events, health fairs, and wellness workshops in their communities — extending the program's reach and normalizing conversations about health.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- J&J Partnership -->
  <section class="section section--cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto; text-align:center;">
        <h2 class="section-title">Partnership with Johnson &amp; Johnson</h2>
        <p style="line-height:1.8; color:var(--text-light); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          The Are You OK? initiative was developed in partnership with Johnson &amp; Johnson, one of the world's leading healthcare companies. This partnership provides Kappa Alpha Psi® with access to leading-edge health education content, clinical expertise, and resources to ensure that the program's guidance is grounded in science and reflective of the latest medical evidence.
        </p>
        <p style="line-height:1.8; color:var(--text-light);">
          Johnson &amp; Johnson's commitment to health equity aligns with Kappa Alpha Psi's mission to improve outcomes for Black men and communities of color — making this partnership a natural expression of shared values.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Crisis Resources -->
  <section class="section section--crimson">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:700px; margin:0 auto; text-align:center;">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color:#FFF8E1;">Crisis Resources</h2>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,248,225,0.85); margin-bottom:2rem; line-height:1.8;">
          If you or a brother is experiencing a mental health crisis, help is available. You are not alone. Please reach out immediately.
        </p>
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius:12px; padding:2rem; border:1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.4);">
          <h3 style="color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:1rem;">NAMI HelpLine</h3>
          <p style="color:#FFF8E1; font-size:1.5rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
            <a href="tel:+18009506264" style="color:#FFF8E1;">800-950-NAMI (6264)</a>
          </p>
          <p style="color:rgba(255,248,225,0.7); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Monday–Friday, 10 AM–10 PM ET</p>
          <div class="divider" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);"></div>
          <p style="color:#FFF8E1; margin-top:1.5rem; margin-bottom:0;">
            Text <strong style="color:var(--gold);">"HelpLine"</strong> to <strong style="color:var(--gold);">62640</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
